{"message":"Implemented the session-scoping fix in `plugins/codex/scripts/codex-companion.mjs` only; no test files were modified.

What changed:
- Added shared local helpers to read `CODEX_COMPANION_SESSION_ID` and filter jobs by the current session.
- Updated `resolveLatestTrackedTaskThread(...)` so `task --resume-last`:
  - checks active tasks only within the current session when a session id is set;
  - selects completed tracked task threads only within the current session when a session id is set;
  - returns no candidate instead of falling back globally when a session id is set and no current-session task exists;
  - preserves the existing global `findLatestTaskThread(...)` fallback when no Claude session id is in scope.
- Updated `task-resume-candidate` to reuse the same session visibility helper, keeping implicit resume and candidate reporting aligned.

Verification performed:
- Created a temporary reproduction script outside the repo that confirmed the pre-fix bug:
  - `task-resume-candidate --json` reported unavailable for `sess-current`.
  - `task --resume-last` still resumed `sess-other`.
  - a running `sess-other` task blocked `sess-current`.
- Re-ran the same verifier after the fix with added edge cases:
  - cross-session completed task is not resumed;
  - other-session running task no longer blocks;
  - current-session completed task still resumes even if another session has a newer task;
  - current-session running task still blocks;
  - no-session global fallback still works.
- Ran full existing tests with a writable temp directory:
  - `TMPDIR=/workspace/repro-tmp npm test`
  - Result: 64/64 passing.

Note: a plain initial `npm test` failed because this environment has a root-owned `/tmp/codex-companion`; using a writable `TMPDIR` avoided that environment-specific permission issue.","summary":"Summarize session-scoped resume fix and verification"}
